      • parseWeatherData

        public WeatherData parseWeatherData​(java.lang.String w)
                             throws java.text.ParseException
        The parseWeatherData() will be invoked by the client to parse the Weather data which is in string format. It will call the concrete implementation of the parse function by concrete WeatherStrategy implementer class.
        Parameters:
        w - weather data instance fetched from the API in string format
        Returns:
        wd returns the parsed results as a Weather Data Object
        Throws:
        java.text.ParseException - indicate a problem with the API, attempt to parse malformed documents, problem while creating or parsing the JSON data.

      • setParser

        public void setParser​(WeatherStrategy jsonStrategyWeatherParser)
        The setParser() sets the concrete implementation strategy for the parsing of weather data.
        Parameters:
        jsonStrategyWeatherParser - instance of weather data
